senses.sense: (historical) An Austrian silver coin equivalent to 20 kreutzers.

A usually sweetened bread enriched with eggs that is baked and then sliced and toasted until dry and crisp; considered easy to digest and therefore given to the ill and used as a teething food for toddlers.
(mineral) A brown to black mineral containing manganese, iron, phosphorus, oxygen, and fluorine.
(chemistry) A molecule, such as an amino acid, that carries both a positive and a negative charge.
Of or pertaining to a zwitterion.
